<div class="hgroup pagewide"><h1 class="title"><span class="title">Mouse reacts with delay before it starts working</span></h1></div>
<div class="region">
<div class="contents pagewide"><p class="p">Wireless and optical mice, as well as touchpads on laptops, may need to
  “wake up” before they start working. They automatically go to sleep when not in
  use to save battery power. To wake up your mouse or touchpad, you can click on
  a mouse button or wiggle the mouse.</p></div>
